{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-collocalia-linchi", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-collocalia-linchi", "name": "穴金丝燕", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-species-collocalia-linchi", "name": "穴金丝燕", "latinName": "Collocalia linchi", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "穴金丝燕（Collocalia linchi）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Cave swiftlet。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -83.68, "y": 918.29, "z": -47.7}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-collocalia", "name": "侏金丝燕属", "latinName": "Collocalia", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "侏金丝燕属（Collocalia）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联10种鸟类，如Pygmy swiftlet、Bornean swiftlet、Christmas Island swiftlet等10种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 10, "x": 417.58, "y": -1.63, "z": -21.36}, {"id": "bird-cave-swiftlet-89613486", "name": "Cave swiftlet", "englishName": "Cave swiftlet", "latinName": "Collocalia linchi", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The cave swiftlet or linchi swiftlet (Collocalia linchi) is a species of swift in the family Apodidae. It is found on the Indonesia islands of Sumatra, Java and Bali. It is a woodland species and nests in caves. The Bornean swiftlet was considered a subspecies, but is now usually considered distinct. Taxonomy The cave swiftlet was described by the naturalists Thomas Horsfield and Frederic Moore in 1854 under the present binomial name Collocalia linchi. The specific epithet linchi is the Javanese word for a swiftlet. There are four recognised subspecies: C. l. dedii Somadikarta, 1986 - Bali and Lombok C. l. linchi Horsfield & Moore, F, 1854 - Bawean and Java C. l. ripleyi Somadikarta, S, 1986 - Barisan Mountains, Sumatra C. l. dodgei Richmond, 1905 - Mt Kinabalu (Sabah), in N Borneo. (now a full species: Collocalia dodgei) Description This bird is shiny blackish-brown above with a greenish gloss, including its rump; sometimes looks black and hooded. Chest black; belly to flanks pale grey with fine black speckles at margins. Wing tips are rounded; underwing is black. Tail black, rounded with shallow notch but lacking the white specks found in the very similar glossy swiftlet (Collocalia esculenta). A distinguishing feature between the two species is that the glossy swiftlet has a tuft of feathers on its hind toe but the cave swiftlet has a naked toe. It is 9 to 11.5 cm (3.5 to 4.5 in) in length. The call is a high-pitched \"cheer-cheer\". Distribution and habitat The cave swiftlet is native to Malaysia and Indonesia. It is found in the Sundaic region, in Java, Madura Island, Bawean, Kangean Island, Nusa Penida, Bali and Lombok, parts of Sumatra, and the western slopes of Mount Kinabalu on Sabah, Borneo. Evidence of it occurring in Malaysia rests on a single specimen in the British Museum labelled \"Molacca\". Its natural habitat is lowland and upland forest and open woodland. Behaviour The cave swiftlet is highly gregarious and flies with all the other species of swift that are sympatric with it. It often circles and flies through the branches of trees emerging through the canopy such as fruiting figs. It breeds in the lighter parts of caves, building a nest of stringy vegetation and cementing the materials to the rock with saliva. Two white, somewhat elongated eggs are laid. Status The cave swiftlet has a very wide range and is common in Java and the nearby islands. It has no particular threats and the IUCN has listed it as being of \"Least Concern\". Although the overall population may be declining slightly, this is not believed to be at such a rate as would justify listing it in a more threatened category. References Further reading Somadikarta, S. (1986). \"Collocalia linchi Horsfield and Moore — a revision\". Bulletin of the British Ornithologists' Club. 106 (1): 32–40. Rheindt, Frank E.; Christidis, Les; Norman, Janette A.; Eaton, James A.; Sadanandan, Keren R.; Schodde, Richard (2017). \"Speciation in Indo-Pacific swiftlets (Aves: Apodidae): integrating molecular and phenotypic data for a new provisional taxonomy of the Collocalia esculenta complex\". Zootaxa. 4250 (5): 401–433. doi:10.11646/zootaxa.4250.5.1. PMID 28609999.", "shortSummary": "The cave swiftlet or linchi swiftlet (Collocalia linchi) is a species of swift in the family Apodidae. It is found on the Indonesia islands…", "locations": ["爪哇岛", "马都拉岛", "巴韋安島", "康厄安群島", "龙目岛", "蘇門答臘島", "京那巴鲁山"], "lat": 6.075, "lng": 116.55861111, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f5/Cave_Swiftlet_%28Collocalia_linchi%29_1.jpg/960px-Cave_Swiftlet_%28Collocalia_linchi%29_1.jpg", "order": "Apodiformes", "family": "Apodidae", "genus": "Collocalia", "species": "Collocalia linchi", "orderCn": "雨燕目", "familyCn": "雨燕科", "genusCn": "侏金丝燕属", "speciesCn": "穴金丝燕", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-apodiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-apodidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-collocalia", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-collocalia-linchi", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-apodiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-apodidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-collocalia", "species": "taxonomy-species-collocalia-linchi"}, "expandable": true, "x": -83.68, "y": 918.29, "z": -32.44}], "links": [{"key": "bird-cave-swiftlet-89613486__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-collocalia-linchi", "source": "bird-cave-swiftlet-89613486", "target": "taxonomy-species-collocalia-linchi", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-collocalia-linchi__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-collocalia", "source": "taxonomy-species-collocalia-linchi", "target": "taxonomy-genus-